Warning, everybody!<br><br>
'Cybergook' exhibits behavior that is similar to what I have seen in wet/dry alcoholics, other substance abusers, and some adults who were severly abused as children.<br><br>
How you handle it is up to you, but you must protect yourself. 'Cybergook' can be very controlling in ways that are not really obvious. Constantly inciting infammatory responses is a form of control. 'Cybergook' may need to do this to try to feel good, elicit sympathy, and justify wallowing in self pity. Passive/agressive, acting out behavior are other characteristics that may be seen once in a while.<br><br>
Some people prefer to ignore 'Cybergook'. That's OK. Others feel the need to respond. That's OK, too. Awareness of what is going on here is what is important. Protect yourself!
